.TH "ti_bandgap_validate" 9 "ti_bandgap_validate" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
ti_bandgap_validate \- helper to check the sanity of a struct ti_bandgap
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" ti_bandgap_validate
.BI "(struct ti_bandgap *bgp "  ","
.BI "int id "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "bgp" 12
struct ti_bandgap pointer
.IP "id" 12
bandgap sensor id
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Checks if the bandgap pointer is valid and if the sensor id is also
applicable.
.SH "RETURN"
0 if no errors, -EINVAL for invalid \fIbgp\fP pointer or -ERANGE if
\fIid\fP cannot index \fIbgp\fP sensors.
